begin_memory_text: In the beginning I asked her about why or how she found Prolific. We started talking about what schools we go to. We shared about what state we live in I believe.
middle_memory_text: We talked a lot about the pandemic and how it has affected our school life. We shared about how the pandemic has affected us mentally and what things we are optimistic or pessimistic about.
end_memory_text: We talked mostly about our living situations and bad roommates we've had. We also talked about how it it a good idea to live with our parents so we can save money on rent.
rest_of_day_open: I think the rest of my week is going to go great. I am looking forward to going to clinicals again especially because I get to see the OR this time. I think I will have a good time in my classes and learning about the new material from my professor.
critical_positive: I think what worked well was that we both had very similar views. We both thought about the same things and we knew how to have a conversation. I think we both sympathized and empathized with each other which really helped the conversation keep going. We were very friendly to each other.
critical_negative: I think what didn't work out well was that we both didn't really know what to say at moments. But this wasn't very often. We also had points where we would overlap or we would mishear what the other person said. With that being said, I don't think there was anything that was too bad.

begin_memory_text: We spoke about where we both lived and what we were doing in terms of school and work. We talked about how we were both doing in terms of the pandemic and how our lives have changed.
middle_memory_text: We spoke about what our plans were for the future and how they were going to look different because of the pandemic. We also talked about the field of study we are both in and what the job market would be like.
end_memory_text: We spoke about roommate experiences and how some of them were pretty bad. We talked about our hopes for the future and how we are trying to stay positive throughout this hard time that the world is going through.
rest_of_day_open: I am looking forward to the rest of the week because I am going to Boston with a friend and am looking forward to some social interaction. I also have a lot of studying to do which puts a damper on the week but it wont be too bad really.
critical_positive: The flow of the conversation went well because we both had some things in common and I found that my partner was very easy to talk to. We both added alot to the conversation and there were no awkward pauses or gaps. It was a great talk all in all.
critical_negative: Everything went very well. The video and audio was clear and there were no disturbances in the conversation. I have nothing negative to say about how the conversation went and I feel it was on the best talks I have had out of the entire experiment. I look forward to speaking with more people.
